      "content": "it's terrifying how easy it would be. if they're using steganography in the kernel, most security software wouldn't even flag it because it looks like legitimate system noise. if someone wanted to actually protect themselves—or start a counter-audit to prove this is happening—what kind of low-level hardware isolation or air-gapping would they even need to implement to stop the harvest? should i be moving everything to an offline environment immediately?",
